cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the analysis of texts using complex networks, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a hybrid classifier that combines statistical paradigms with networked models, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) communities. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with the analysis of text complexity, which is a common topic in information retrieval (IR) and search engines. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of networks, which is a common topic in the social and information sciences. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category.
